  "prompt": "What does Accent do to food?",
  "response": "Accent is a brand name for monosodium glutamate (MSG), a flavor enhancer commonly used in cooking. MSG enhances the savory taste of foods and can make dishes more flavorful. It works by stimulating the umami taste receptors on the tongue, which can amplify the natural flavors in various ingredients, particularly in meats, vegetables, and broths.\n\nWhile MSG is generally recognized as safe by food regulatory authorities, some people report sensitivity to it, experiencing symptoms such as headaches or nausea, commonly referred to as \"MSG symptom complex.\" It\u2019s important for individuals with sensitivities to be aware of its presence in food products.",
